<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 06 at 9:38AM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL AFFECT
EASTERN ROCKINGHAM...CASWELL AND SOUTH CENTRAL PITTSYLVANIA COUNTIES
AND THE CITY OF DANVILLE...
At 937 AM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was located over Reidsville,
moving northeast at 40 mph.
Winds in excess of 30 mph are possible with this storm. Rainfall up
to 0.50 inch are possible with this storm.
Locations impacted include...
Danville...
Reidsville...
Wentworth...
Yanceyville...
Bethel...
Camp Springs...
and Providence.
Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</description>
